        <div xml:id="Kali8-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">itu collātu piriyaluṟṟa talaivaṉ kuṟippaṟintu tōḻi poruḷatu 
            nilaiyāmai kūṟi avaḷoṭu kūṭic celkiṉṟa ilvāḻkkaic celavē poruḷeṉa avaṉ celavaḻuṅkak kūṟiyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en"/>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="Kali8">
            <lg type="edition">
                <l>naṭuvikan torīi nayaṉillāṉ viṉaivāṅkak</l>
                <l>koṭitōrtta maṉṉavaṉ kōlpōla ñāyiṟu</l>
                <l>kaṭukupu katirmūṭṭik kāyciṉan teṟutali</l>
                <l>ṉuṟalūṟu kamaḻkaṭāt tolkiya veḻilvēḻam</l>
                <l>vaṟaṉuḻu nāñcilpōṉ maruppūṉṟi nilañcēra</l>
                <l>viṟaṉmalai vempiya pōkkaru veñcurañ</l>
                <l>collā tiṟappat tuṇintaṉirk koruporuḷ</l>
                <l>colluva tuṭaiyēṉ kēṇmiṉmaṟ ṟaiiya;</l>
                <l rend="space">vīḻunark kiṟaicciyāy viralkavar picaikkuṅkō</l> <!-- metrical and wordsplit don't match 
                  picaikkuṅkō vs. icaikkum kōl; I don't change this however as this doesn't upset the lines -->
                <l>lēḻuntam payaṉkeṭa viṭainiṉṟa narampaṟūum</l>
                <l>yāḻiṉu nilaiyilāp poruḷaiyu naccupavō;</l>
                <l rend="space">marīittāṅ koṇṭāraik koṇṭakkāṟ pōlātu</l>
                <l>piriyuṅkāṟ piṟareḷḷap pīṭiṉṟip puṟamāṟun</l>
                <l>tiruviṉu nilaiyilāp poruḷaiyu naccupavō;</l>
                <l rend="space">puraitavap payaṉōkkār tammākka muyalvārai</l>
                <l>varaiviṉṟic ceṟumpoḻutiṟ kaṇṇōṭā tuyirvauvu</l>
                <l>maraiciṉu nilaiyilāp poruḷaiyu naccupavō;</l>
                <l rend="space">eṉavāṅku,</l>
                <l>naccal kūṭātu peruma viccela</l>
                <l>voḻital vēṇṭuval cūḻiṟ paḻiyiṉṟu</l>
                <l>maṉṉavaṉ puṟantara varuvirun tōmpit</l>
                <l>taṉṉakar viḻaiyak kūṭi</l>
                <l>ṉiṉṉuṟal viyaṉmārpa vatumaṉum poruḷē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="7a-c">            To you who, without saying [anything], resolved to traverse </l>
<l corresp="6">the hot desert difficult to walk where the victorious mountains are hot </l>
<l corresp="4">so that the handsome elephant bull that is weakened by the oozing, fragrant musth he experiences </l>
<l corresp="5">joins the ground, leaning on [its] tusk like a plough ploughing dry soil, </l>
<l corresp="2">because the sun, like the sceptre of a king that is regarded as cruel </l>
<l corresp="1">when dragging to work someone without longing, trangressing [and] foresaking justice, </l>
<l corresp="3">made haste, kindled [its] rays [and] scorched with burning anger, </l>
<l corresp="7d-8">I have one thing to say, listen, o lord: </l>
<l rend="space">Those who fall, </l>
<l>will they desire wealth that is no more stable that the lute</l>
<l>on which the string that stood in the middle is severed so that the yield of all the seven notes</l>
<l>is lost that sounds when fingers seize [them] pleasingly to them?</l>
<l rend="space">And will they desire wealth that is no more stable than Fortune</l>
<l>who changes to the outside without greatness, while others censure at the time it parts,</l>
<l>unlike the time it took those who jointly took?</l>
<l rend="space">And will they desire wealth that is no more stable than a king</l>
<l>who life is snatched away without pity at the time he subdued without limit</l>
<l>those who struggle for their gain, being ones who don’t look at much such benefit?</l>
<l rend="space">That is to say,</l>
<l rend="space">It is impossible, great man, to long for this going.</l>
<l>If you consider I must stay behind there is no blame.</l>
<l>If a king protectively protects the coming feast</l>
<l>[and thus] meets the desires of his town,</l>
<l>o man with a wide chest sweet to have, that is wealth.</l>
            </lg>
